##Complexity and complexity of resuming work

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Migrant Workers Queue on a platform to board a special train to resume work at a factory in Shaoxing, Zhejiang Province, on Feb. 23,2010 at the Chongqing North Railway Station. Xinhua news agency, Wang Quanchao

This article is about 4282 words long

Estimated reading time: 11 minutes

Author | Zhongqingbao Zhongqingwang journalist, Cheng Mengchao

Editor | from Yuhua

One village official said he had been on a roller coaster for more than 40 days.

At first, yes. A week before the Spring Festival, migrant workers began driving home, crowding the narrow village roads. He smiled unconsciously and felt that the two years of poverty reduction had borne fruit.

It's not GonNa be funny much longer. On the 29th day of the 12th lunar month, the streets were suddenly deserted. "It was even colder than usual. "

When the country is quiet, the countryside has its "bloom moment" : Local "hard core" closure of the village, road closure did block the virus, the vast and sparsely populated rural areas more secure, "or home better" .

Now the flowers are in bloom and spring ploughing is about to begin. The old people sit in the sun again at the entrance of the village; The villagers ask the cadres, "when will it be completely restored? "

After a few days of rejoicing, new problems began to pile up.

A resident cadre in Shaanxi Province has mobilized villagers to work in Nantong, Jiangsu Province, arranging free charter flights. No one in the village has signed up, and people want to return to their cities to work.

In Yunnan, a cadre in the middle of the night received a phone call, the caller is his organization to a county in Zhejiang collective migrant villagers. It was raining when we arrived. At one point, no one came to pick us up, and many people got wet. Later, the local authorities told us that there was a problem with the demand docking. There was no position at the moment, so we had to stay in the hotel.

A party secretary in Baicheng, Jilin Province, dare not miss a phone call in recent days. The village 80 tons of garlic unsalable, he will own mobile phone number to the Internet, more than once with high expectations to answer the call, the other side asked: can send 10 Jin?

1

When told to go door-to-door, Sun Xiong, a village cadre in Zhaotong, Yunnan, and his colleagues had not yet prepared masks. Until now, Sun Xiong a mask to wear two or three days, "basic enough. "

Checkpoints were quickly set up between the roads of the villages. There was a lot of snow in the mountains and it took a few days for the tents to arrive. Sun Xiong remembered that there was a card shop next to a house, and there was a stove outside the gate. The old cadre can not support, crouch on the door of somebody else endures heating.

A village official in Xingtai, Hebei Province, recalled that they had initially closed only the main road, and that a team from above had come to inspect it and said that the back roads could be moved. Short-handed, he had to beg the villagers for barbed wire and block the way. Later, the leadership came to secretly visit, found that some of the checkpoints did not ewen gun. Only Mercury-in-glass thermometer, a large number of people, less than measurement, there will be omissions, and was "strictly rectified. ".

In Ensch, the village's first secretary, Ding Rui, had not been home for more than 40 days and often worked until after 11 p.m. In addition to routine screening, patrols, statements, Shouka, the village of more than 70-year-old Gout, as well as maternal labor, have to take care to send through the checkpoint. Every three days, the cadres go to the city to buy the daily necessities that the villagers need.

At night, Ding Rui and his colleagues beat a flashlight in the village patrol, see 10 o'clock after the light of the family, to knock on the door to ask, worried about dinner and gambling. But the past month has been dominated by family feuds. There was a fight between the husband and wife, and both of their friends and relatives came. Police intervention found that the cause is not to return to work, car loans are stacked in front of the women suspect men "no future. ".

"everyone has been holding back at home for too long, " Ding said.

Tan Zhangwei, the Party secretary of another village, also in Ensch, often drives to patrol the countryside at night. Some villagers persist in visiting relatives, while the night to go up the mountain road, want to get through the customs. It was dark in the mountains at night, and the headlights could see for miles. When someone is spotted, they unconsciously roll to the side of the road or run to a nearby field. Since the Spring Festival, he has stopped four or five groups of people.

"I'm so tired of looking over my shoulder. "

'He did his best, but he was always worried that something was missing, ' Tan said. If someone gets infected, it's on them.

Sun Xiong with the railway department feedback "Wuhan Return Personnel List" door-to-door verification, there are always villagers do not recognize, after all, to house isolation for 14 days. The final trick is "scare" : When you return to the car found a suspected case, very dangerous.

After the Fifteenth Day of the first lunar month, the checkpoints in Sun Xiong's township were removed, and the people were able to buy food and seek medical treatment. The number of people visiting relatives and friends has also increased. For the first few days, the town received four or five reports a day -- a return trip to a house under quarantine.

There's only one way to do it: 14 days. But each household is isolated, with three staff members: Village doctors, supervisors, and a food delivery, "administrative resources occupied too much. "

By March, the work theme began to change from "strict prevention and strict control" to "back to work and back to production. Sun Xiong and his colleagues were given a new assignment. The town has registered about 5,000 returning workers and has urged more than 4,000 of them to leave for work recently.

So far, about half of the migrant workers in Sun's mountainous township have stayed home.

"difficult. " Sun Xiong wry smile in the telephone.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Village officials from a village in Ensch, Hubei Province, went to a villager's home to take his temperature on a snowy day. Photo courtesy of interviewees

2

Jiang Yong (not his real name) and dozens of fellow villagers from the mountains of Yunnan came to a county in the east, taking the "point-to-point" migrant bus organized between the two places. More than 30 hours away, he only ate two bowls of instant noodles. But for a time, he was looking forward to his new life.

The posters circulating in the mountains show him entering an electronics factory with modern equipment. The data that the village cadre issues shows, protect bottom salary 5000-6500 yuan, have air conditioning and independent toilet; do full 3 months, still have 1200 yuan to stabilize a post subsidy. When they set off, a deputy district chief of the city personally put them on the bus. All of this reassured him.

Arriving shortly after 5 am, a group of people were left at the entrance to the accommodation area. About three hours later, someone drives up, says he's from the agency. Jiang Yong and others into the dormitory, the heart is cool: the House is full of garbage, the toilet is blocked.

They inquired with the factory's old staff, worked for three months, the bonus should be 4000 yuan. There was speculation that the agency would take a cut and quit. Like Jiang Yong. He's looking for another job. Still have the identity card of a few townsman to be in intermediary there, say is to want to leave, have to pay 750 yuan road fare.

A township official in Jiang Yong's hometown confirmed the story to reporters. "The task is heavy and the time is tight, " the official explained. "To a large extent, the government and enterprises have not done a good job of butt-checking each other. Some information is not verified. If a company exaggerates Haikou, the government will believe it. "

The dilemma for Ding Rui of Ensch, Hubei Province, is that more and more villagers want to return to work. "hold on a dozen more days. " That's the word on the lips these days. The periphery has not appeared the case for a long time, the question "when to recover" the people are more and more.

In Sun Xiong's town, the number of people gathering to play cards is also increasing. When they went to deal with it, the rebuttals were similar: You pulled the plug, encouraged a return to work, why didn't you let them play cards?

After the Spring Festival, some small shops and clinics in rural Xingtai were allowed to stay open for a few hours a day to maintain people's livelihood. Colleagues immediately went to town and asked: they can drive, why can't we drive?

"Many businessmen are anxious, " said the village official in Xingtai.

Of these, I am afraid that farmers are particularly anxious. In Hangzhou, Zhejiang Province, 20,000 unsold orchids are selling for less than 50% off; in Pingtan County, a farmer's 700 Mu of scallions will rot by April. A party secretary in Handan, Hebei Province, paid 35,000 yuan to buy all the village's unsold eggs and distribute them to the elderly.

Some e-commerce practitioners had concluded in an interview earlier that there were three reasons for the serious unsalable sales of agricultural products during the epidemic: First, the agricultural trade and other trading centers were closed, and the offline channels for agricultural products, which had long been relied on, almost stopped; second, the roads were closed during the epidemic prevention, logistics Difficulties; third, because of the shutdown, packaging and delivery of cardboard boxes, labor shortages.

In Dongfeng Cun, Baicheng, more than 20 farmers'homes have a combined 80 tonnes of garlic unsold. Party secretary Ban Liping said, the most important issue is logistics and transportation, the previous hot foreign dealers are not to come.

The anxious secretary posted his contact information online and has received more than 30 phone calls in the past few days. There are two supermarkets called, I heard that the village varieties and Shandong garlic different, garlic small, more suitable for hair garlic, garlic, did not have interest. Some people want to buy 3500 Jin, driving a car to come over, Ben Liping took them around the village. The quiet street soon gushes out the unsalable peasant household, "how, secretary, came a person? "

In a month, the garlic will be rotten. The good news is that road restrictions are gradually being relaxed, some merchants began to call for advice. Dongfeng Cun is now in a race against time. Benliping ponders, this year even if some cheap, the villagers do not lose money on it.

In Sun Xiong's town, the village loudspeakers have been shouting "resume production" all day long recently, and cadres have been knocking on doors to persuade them.

The problem is that workers are reluctant to change places of work. Zhejiang, Jiangsu, Guangdong and other places sent a lot of demand for labor, often hundreds of people. But most of the villagers still want to continue the work before the festival, are waiting for the notice of the boss to resume work. It's got friends and connections, a familiar life.

"What's more, a person who used to be a mechanic has become a skilled mechanic. Now let him do electronics and relearn. What if he's not good at it? He'll feel like he's taking a risk, " Sun said.

The spring planting has begun. If there is no epidemic, we will return to work after years, the land at home to the elderly species. But now, many young and middle-aged people are still at home, thinking not to let the old suffer, simply plant the land and then go.

Sun Xiong most "hate iron not into steel" , is to stay for a long time with inert people, said not out, at home to engage in farming. Sun Xiong raised breeding matters needing attention, the other side ask three do not know, obviously in perfunctory.

The village official in Xingtai, Hebei Province, said conditions in his town were good and there was little pressure to resume work. There are a lot of factories nearby, the villagers near the migrant workers, in and out of the village to take a temperature on the line, most of the work.

The head of a work team in a Shaanxi village told the reporter that the desks of the village committee offices are now covered with posters for recruitment in the Jiangsu and Zhejiang regions, but in the past, migrant workers in the county mainly went to Xi'an, Shanbei and Xinjiang, many businesses in these areas are not yet open.

3

Life goes on. Sun Xiong found that the recent traffic, shopping is not too convenient, the village will have four or five villagers, driving a small truck, to the town wholesale fruits and vegetables, pull back to the village to sell.

To these new business that germinates quietly, cadre also pondered, should intervene, feel finally give up. They are unorthodox, but they do make it easier for the elderly; they are run by villagers, and seem safer than going to distant towns to buy from each family.

In Shaanxi, the captain's village is bustling as never before. Because the epidemic has not returned to work young people are not idle, with the village people to help each other, many families built up the house. A batch of housing in the village are built in the past few years when poverty alleviation, the standard to comply with, the area is not large. Over the years, many people have made money, have bought cement and sand pile at home. Not Allowed to go out during the Spring Festival, the family are crowded in the 15-square-meter kitchen fire, the expansion of the heart is even more.

At present, the village rules, work must wear a mask, can not eat together. Cadres from time to time to stare, the work captain said, look at the eyes quite happy. This time of year, the village young people have long gone, but now has some New Year's day-like popularity.

The spring ploughing season has also arrived in Hubei. Nearly every day, Tan drives to the town to help the villagers pay their water and electricity bills, to the butcher shop to cut meat, and to buy medicine for the elderly and stationery for the children. The new task is, the statistics of each spring planting agricultural means of production, unified distribution by the agricultural technology station in town. In his village, by 2020, the seeds will be planted.

Sun Xiong remembered that during the Spring Festival, when it snowed heavily, he was on duty at the checkpoint. He was so thirsty that day, he didn't have a canteen, so he muttered something. There was an old man with a limp who said nothing and turned to go home. Sun Xiong also did not notice, did not want to 20 minutes later, the old man from home a cup of hot water, and a limp back, "you hard, always have a drink of water. "

The township official in Jiang Yong's hometown told the China Youth Daily's China Youth Daily Online reporter that he felt most strongly about what happened to the villagers while they were working. "They trusted us to go, and we really wanted to help them, " he said

Jiang Yong and his wife work in Kunming before the holiday. They rented a whole house there and lived like a family. They recently built a house in their hometown and owe some money. They think the income in the East is higher. He wanted to verify the new job information, in fact, peace of mind, it will be fine, but has not been waiting for the Eastern County officials. The good news is, the head of the Township Labor Insurance Office is coming to help them.

The cadres in my hometown said that from now on, each group of people working collectively will be sent by the government, and the staff will return after they have settled down.

A lot of times, help comes in handy. In Shaoyang, the government arranged media filming for a farm that had a slow market of 30,000 catties of quail eggs. After the video was released, eggs that had been on the market for a month were sold out in two days. The frightened hostess said: Thank You, thank you, 200,000 yuan of goods, we almost collapsed.

A rural woman in Huangzhou, Hubei Province, with a child suffering from severe mental illness, became the family's sole labor force after her husband's accidental fall to death and eventually became an "expert in poverty alleviation. ". But this past winter, she added 30,000 unsold eggs, enough to drag her back into the abyss.

The village official in charge of helping her edited the online help-seeking message, and seven hours after it was sent out, the Huangzhou people bought up all her eggs. When the goods were handed over, the peasant woman could hardly speak. That night, the village official spent two hours sending Thanksgiving messages to everyone in the city who bought eggs.

Ding Rui is waiting for the day when the ban in Hubei will be lifted. He wasn't too worried about what he was going to do. Standing in the field, looking at the three or two people have been working in their own fields, he still believes that this winter has gone through, everything will be better.
